<subSubSection id="C366657DFFA64407D3EBFCA0FC5DFA22" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA64407D3EBFCA0FEC5FCE8" blockId="4.[151,791,813,876]" box="[151,281,849,876]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
(
<figureCitation id="13472A73FFA64407D3E3FCA0FECDFCE8" box="[159,273,849,876]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[209,1371,192,1872]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[201,1386,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–15. 9. HOLOTYPE ♀ Mimonephelotes enganensis Breuning, 1970, habitus (photo: G. Chemin); 10. ditto, lateral view (photo: G. Chemin); 11. ditto, labels (photo: G. Chemin); 12. HT ♀ Anhammus luzonicus Breuning, 1982, habitus (photo: G. Chemin); 13. ditto, lateral view (photo: G. Chemin); 14. ditto, labels (photographed by: G. Chemin); 15. ♂ Nephelotus enganensis, habitus (Photo: G. Chemin)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577769" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577769/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Figs 9–15</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA64407D3EBFC65FD0CFB9F" blockId="4.[151,1437,916,1447]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B07FFA64407D3EBFC65FE8DFC2A" author="Breuning, S. von" box="[151,337,916,942]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" pagination="363 - 377" refId="ref4097" refString="Breuning, S. von (1970) Nouveaux Coleopteres Cerambycidae Lamiinae des Collections du Museum de Paris (suite). Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris (2 eme serie) 42 (2), 363 - 377." type="journal article" year="1970">Breuning (1970)</bibRefCitation>
did not compare 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D169FC65FD12FC2A" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1970" box="[533,718,916,942]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimonephelotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D169FC65FD12FC2A" box="[533,718,916,942]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Mimonephelotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D18EFC65FCACFC2A" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[754,880,916,942]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D18EFC65FCACFC2A" box="[754,880,916,942]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D0C3FC65FBE7FC2A" baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[959,1083,916,942]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D0C3FC65FBE7FC2A" box="[959,1083,916,942]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, stating that it differs from it in the shorter lateral pronotal spine and in the presence of a short carina on each elytral base. This carina is, in reality, a double series of tubercles located on a bulge similar in all to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D001FC2CFBC5FC72" baseAuthorityName="J. Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[893,1049,989,1014]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conspersus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D001FC2CFBC5FC72" box="[893,1049,989,1014]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">N. conspersus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D740FC2CFB1BFC72" box="[1084,1223,989,1014]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D740FC2CFB1FFC72" authorityName="Vitali &amp; Chemin" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Newman" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[1084,1219,989,1014]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marcipor">N. marcipor</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Thus, the provided characters are just typical of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D137FBF1FD15FB9E" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[587,713,1024,1050]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D137FBF1FD15FB9E" box="[587,713,1024,1050]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA64407D3BBFBD4FD40FB4A" blockId="4.[151,1437,916,1447]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
However, this taxon from Luzon clearly differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D065FBD4FC7CFBBA" authorityName="Vitali &amp; Chemin" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Newman" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[793,928,1061,1086]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marcipor">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D065FBD4FC7CFBBA" box="[793,928,1061,1086]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">N. marcipor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The body size is more robust and larger (
<quantity id="4C849B13FFA64407D60AFBD5FF3BFBE7" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" unit="mm" value="23.0" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="19.0">19- 27 mm</quantity>
vs 
<quantity id="4C849B13FFA64407D26CFBB9FE56FBE7" box="[272,394,1096,1123]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" unit="mm" value="21.0" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="19.0">19-23 mm</quantity>
), the basal granulation of elytra forms distinct rows separated by smooth areas, the humeral tubercle is longer and finally, the pronotal disc is densely punctate (rather than smooth) at sides. Moreover, it differs from the Luzon population of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D294FB60FDB3FB2E" authorityName="Vitali &amp; Chemin" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Newman" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[488,623,1169,1194]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marcipor">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D294FB60FDB3FB2E" box="[488,623,1169,1194]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">N. marcipor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the pronotal tubercles twice as long as wide. These characters support the validity of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D247FB44FE04FB4A" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1970" box="[315,472,1205,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimonephelotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="enganensis">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D247FB44FE04FB4A" box="[315,472,1205,1230]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">N. enganensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a true species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA64407D3BBFB29FF3AFA07" blockId="4.[151,1437,916,1447]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B07FFA64407D3BBFB29FE5FFB76" author="Breuning, S. von" box="[199,387,1240,1266]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" pagination="77 - 78" refId="ref4141" refString="Breuning, S. von (1971) Quelques rectifications systematiques sur les Lamiaires (Col. Cerambycidae). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de Mulhouse, 1971, 77 - 78. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / bsef. 1972.21237" type="journal article" year="1971">Breuning (1971)</bibRefCitation>
introduced 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D171FB29FD66FB76" baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[525,698,1240,1266]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimanhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D171FB29FD66FB76" box="[525,698,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Mimanhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as substitute name for 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D0BBFB29FB5CFB76" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1970" box="[967,1152,1240,1266]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimonephelotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D0BBFB29FB5CFB76" box="[967,1152,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Mimonephelotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, claiming that this name was preoccupied. Actually, the name in question was 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D182FB0DFBA8FA92" authority="Breuning, 1940" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1940" box="[766,1140,1276,1302]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimonephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D182FB0DFC65FA92" box="[766,953,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Mimonephelotus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B07FFA64407D0BDFB0DFBA8FA92" author="Breuning, S. von" box="[961,1140,1276,1302]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" pagination="115 - 214" refId="ref3945" refString="1 - 322 pp. Breuning, S. von (1940) Novae species Cerambycidarum. IX. Folia Zoologica et Hydrobiologica, 10 (1), 115 - 214. Breuning, S. von (1943) Etudes sur les Lamiaires (Coleop. Cerambycidae). Douzieme tribu: Agniini Thomson. Novitates Entomologicae, 3 eme supplement, (89), 133 - 144. Breuning, S. von (1944 a) Etudes sur les Lamiaires (Coleop. Cerambycidae). Douzieme tribu: Agniini Thomson. Novitates Entomologicae, 3 eme supplement: (134), 497 - 504." type="journal article" year="1940">Breuning, 1940</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which differs by one letter (
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D3BAFAD1FE4EFABE" box="[198,402,1312,1338]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Mimonephelot-e-s</emphasis>
vs. 
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D2BEFAD1FD53FABE" box="[450,655,1312,1338]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Mimonephelot-u-s</emphasis>
); thus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D19BFAD1FC48FABE" baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[743,916,1312,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimanhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D19BFAD1FC48FABE" box="[743,916,1312,1338]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Mimanhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an unnecessary replacement name. Finally, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B07FFA64407D3EBFAB5FE8FFADA" author="Breuning, S. von" box="[151,339,1348,1374]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" pagination="9 - 29" refId="ref4226" refString="Breuning, S. von (1982) Diagnoses preliminaires de nouveaux Lamiinae du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris [Coleoptera, Cerambycidae]. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, (New Series) 18 (1), 9 - 29." type="journal article" year="1982">Breuning (1982)</bibRefCitation>
described this species for a second time as 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D036FAB5FBE5FADA" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1982" box="[842,1081,1348,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luzonicus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D036FAB5FBE5FADA" box="[842,1081,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Anhammus luzonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based again on a female from Luzon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA64407D3BBFA7CFC5DFA22" blockId="4.[151,1437,916,1447]" box="[199,897,1420,1447]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">In conclusion, the following taxonomic changes are proposed:</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C366657DFFA64407D3EBFA3EFAACF945" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA64407D3EBFA3EFE6CFA6D" blockId="4.[151,722,1487,1657]" box="[151,432,1487,1513]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D3EBFA3EFE6CFA6D" authority="Pascoe, 1866" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[151,432,1487,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D3EBFA3EFEC9FA6D" box="[151,277,1487,1513]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Nephelotus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B07FFA64407D260FA3EFE6CFA6D" author="Pascoe, F. P." box="[284,432,1487,1513]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" pagination="225 - 336" refId="ref4447" refString="Pascoe, F. P. (1866) Longicornia Malayana; or, a Descriptive Catalogue of the Species of the three Longicorn Families Lamiidae, Cerambycidae and Prionidae collected by Mr. A. R. Wallace in the Malay Archipelago. (Part III). The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 3 (3) 3, 225 - 336, pls X-XV." type="journal article" year="1866">Pascoe, 1866</bibRefCitation>
